name: Benevolent Jewels $25 E-Gift Card
description:
Convenient for you and easy for them, our e-gift cards are perfect for any fashionista! 

Benevolent Jewels e-gift cards are sent via email. The recipient of the e-gift card must have a valid email address. They will receive an email including their e-gift card promo code number. E-gift cards do not have an expiration date and you will not be charged shipping for the e-gift card purchase.

If you would like for us to include a personalized message and send your e-gift card on a special day, email us at BenevolentJewels@gmail.com. 

Similar to other purchases, you will receive an email confirmation once the e-gift card is sent to the recipient.

name: Silver Initial Necklace for Barrio Dogs
description:
You can now personalize a necklace that will give back to others! Our stunning initial necklaces include a silver-plated charm that can also be easily added to your favorite bracelet. The back is handcrafted with a sparkling Swarovski crystal that is offered in one of our signature colors--pink or blue. The classic, block style and versatile clasp will make this charm always be in style!

PLEASE READ: After you have completed your purchase, please fill out our "Monogram & Initial Form" on our website. This form can be located in our bottom navigation bar. All engraving sales are final.

When engraving your initials, Lilly Georgia Collins will be engraved as LGC or Brooke Taylor will be engraved as BT.

Charm Information: 
♦ 1" diameter approx. 
♦ Engraved front initials 
♦ Engraved back with cause's name 
♦ Silver-plated 
♦ Swarovski crystal accent 
♦ Spring clasp

Necklace Information: 
♦ 18" rolo chain 
♦ 925 Italian sterling silver 
♦ Lobster clasp

Barrio Dogs will receive 20% of the profits from this purchase. Barrio Dogs aims to raise awareness of available low-cost sterilization for pets, responsible animal care, and prevention of crimes against animals under the State of Texas animal cruelty statutes. For more information about Barrio Dogs, please visit www.BarrioDogs.org.
